    <h1 class="hed">A Coronavirus Mystery: Why Are There So Few Cases in South Asia?</h1>
</span>
<h2 class="dek-heading">India, Pakistan, and Bangladesh are home to nearly a quarter of the world’s population but account for only 2 percent of confirmed cases of COVID-19.</h2>
<div class="meta-data ">
    <address class="author-list">
    <span class="pre">By</span>
    <a
        href="https://foreignpolicy.com/author/ravi-agrawal/"
        rel="author"
        class="author">
    Ravi Agrawal</a></address>
    <span class="separator">|</span>
    <time
    pubdate
    datetime="2020-04-30"
    title="April 30th, 2020"
    class="date-time">
April 30, 2020, 4:52 PM</time>
</div>




				<figure class="figure-image ">
